{
  "texts": [
    "The pan-European \"Agreement on Reforming Research Assessment\" asked signatories to commit to moving away from metrics such as impact factor and the h-index in assessing researchers for jobs, promotions, and grants (48).",
    "Efforts of this kind are not confined to Europe.",
    "The Declaration on Research Assessment (DORA; https://sfdora.org/about-dora/), established in 2012, is dedicated to improving the evaluation of scholarly research outputs.",
    "DORA's primary goals include increasing awareness of innovative assessment tools and facilitating the adoption of responsible metrics in hiring, promotion, and funding decisions.",
    "DORA has evolved into a global initiative encompassing all academic disciplines."
  ]
}